  <programme start="20260513150500 +0000" stop="20260513160500 +0000" channel="unknown.unifitv">
    <title lang="en">Where The Legend Begins</title>
    <desc lang="en">FOU (CHOI SIU FUN, ADA) is a beauty living in the time of the Three Kingdoms. A legendary military strategist, CAO CAO (LAU DAN), treats her family well because of her. Everyone is stunned by her beauty, including CAO's sons, PEI (CHAN HO), who is a powerful warrior and will do anything for FOU; and ZHI (MA CHUN WAI, STEVEN), who is intelligent and a good lover. FOU likes them both at first, but she finds out that PEI is a mean person and decides to love ZHI. However, CAO makes her into a political pawn by arranging for her to marry PEI, in order to keep PEI happy. Although she is reluctant, she has to follow CAO's order. Ever after that, ZHI loses his interest in living. PEI becomes the emperor after CAO dies. He worries that ZHI will eventually overthrow him and tries to harm him all the time. Later, PEI is taken in by a rumour that his son is actually ZHI's and he poisons FOU out of rage. ZHI is exiled. Even after PEI dies, his son still does not approve ZHI's return. ZHI loses all his hope in returning to his own country. When he reaches the sea, he sees a goddess, whom he believes is FOU, dancing in the water in the haze. He writes the renowned story of 'Where The Legend Begins' to memorialize their love.</desc>
    <category lang="en">Drama Series</category>
    <episode-num system="xmltv_ns">0.6.</episode-num>
    <episode-num system="onscreen">S1E7</episode-num>
